b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Amie and Sunsama share a solid foundation of core features including Task Management, Ai Assistant, Calendar, Integrations. Where Amie pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Collaboration, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Sunsama uniquely offers Analytics, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Amie holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Sunsama scores 7/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Amie offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Sunsama's starting price of $20/mo. Amie has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Sunsama does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
