f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Amie is best suited for professionals, freelancers, calendar power users, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Sunsama, meanwhile, shines for individuals, executives, mindful workers, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, Amie describes itself as \"Joyful calendar app combining scheduling, tasks, and availability sharing.\" Sunsama, established in 2016, positions itself as \"Calm daily planner that pulls tasks from all your tools into one focused view.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Amie** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Sunsama is a poor choice — far from it. Sunsama excels in its own right, particularly for individuals and executives.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value beautiful and joyful design, go with Amie. If beautiful daily planning ritual matters more to you, Sunsama is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
